<DOC><DOCNO> AP890503-0181 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-03-89 1836EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Bush-Harvard     05-03 0152</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Bush-Harvard,150</SECOND><HEAD>Bush Praisess Harvard Hockey</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Bush, a onetime Yale Universitybaseball captain, put aside old loyalties Wednesday to congratulatethe Harvard championship hockey team.   Bush invited members of the Ivy League squad to the White HouseRose Garden, where he greeted the players and swapped jokes coachBill Cleary and others. He also greeted former Democratic Partychairman Paul Kirk, who is Cleary's brother-in-law, after crackinga joke about Kirk's party affiliation.   ``You talk about turning the other cheek,'' the president saidas he walked amidst the Harvard athletes. ``But they're the champsand I salute them.''   Bush was presented with a Harvard running suit and a Harvardhockey uniform and two hockey sticks.   Just after somone raised a question about whether the Yalealumnus would ever be seen in Harvard clothing, Bush quipped that``I'm going to take my loot and get out of here.''</TEXT></DOC>